$ Office Object Model: Excel - Workbook.windows

It is possible to open multiple windows on or for the same → Microsoft/Office/Excel/Object-Model/Workbook. This makes it possible to work on different regions
in a → Microsoft/Office/Excel/Object-Model/Worksheet or different worksheets side by side.

The collection of windows is stored in the workbook's `windows` property. The following statement prints the number of windows on a workbook:
code {
debug.print (→ Microsoft/Office/Excel/Object-Model/Application/index#excel-application-active-objects[activeWorkbook].windows.count)
code }

{ Creating a new window

  A new windows is created on the ribbon's *View* tab and then clicking *New Window*:
  gh|about-Excel|/ribbon/View/New-Window.png||

  In → development/languages/VBA[Visual Basic for Applications], a new window can be created like so:
code {
activeWorkbook.newWindow
code }

}
